summary: I’ve been reading through and listening to all the HS1 promo again and the Cameron Crowe podcast has so many fascinating...
body:
I’ve been reading through and listening to all the HS1 promo again and the Cameron Crowe podcast has so many fascinating anecdotes. He says before the RS interview he didn’t really know anything about Harry so he’d gone early to the studio to wait for him “to try and catch the vibe” and while waiting he was thinking about the Joan Didion story from The White Album (which is fab btw, go read it) about The Doors where Jim Morrison turns up at a studio in a scary mood and just being odd in general:

“Morrison sits down on the leather couch again and leans back. He lights a match. He studies the flame a while and then very slowly, very deliberately, lowers it to the fly of his black vinyl pants. Manzarek watches him. The girl who is rubbing Manzarek’s shoulders does not look at anyone. There is a sense that no one is going to leave the room ever. It will be some weeks before the Doors finish recording this album. I do not see it through.”

So Cameron’s expecting some kind of overhyped, tortured popstar to walk in but what happens is he gets a text from a super enthusiastic and endearing Harry, excited about the interview and what they’re going to do, and Cameron’s laughing his head off because Harry is so eager and happy about his new band and making the album that he won’t stop talking about it. So Cameron has hours of a chatty, rambling, animated Harry on record, which unfortunately we’ll probably never have access to :(
